Laikipia speaker Patrick Mariru has said he will run for Laikipia West MP against incumbent Wachira Karani. Mariru said Laikipia politics will be issue-based, with the voters&rsquo; interests taking the centre stage next year.&ldquo;We will engage in the politics of water, roads, hospitals and education,&rdquo; he said. Mariru spoke during a fundraiser presided over by Deputy President William Ruto at 91 Municipality Primary School, Nyahururu, on Saturday.He said, however, he will support the MP during his remaining term in office. &ldquo;Whoever wins will shake the loser&rsquo;s hand,&rdquo; Mariru said. In response, Karani who was present, said the voters will decide when the time comes.